<br />

<br />
I have to agree with this assessment.  Those arms sell really well and for about half that price you could get Plate arms with similar stats for about half what you can sell the Hardened Flesh.
<br />

<br />
You can sell the Architec's Scepter for about 2k or so and use the Troubadours Mace.  Both weapons are pretty much equal but Troub Mace has a nice Brass mod.  Unless you just have to have the pretty sparklies.  With that 2k for the scepter, and the 7k for the sleeves (depending on server) you can easily upgrade both wrists.  Or you can go farm the items and have a smith do the combines for you for new wrists, up to you.  
<br />

<br />
Rigid Steelweave Sleeves are about 4k (if you farm the stuff you could very likely get em smithed for you for about 1k)
<br />

<br />
Rigid Steelweave Bracers about 3.5k each. (once again farm the items you could get it done for about 1kish.)
<br />

<br />
The Enchanted Sash of Wonder:
<br />
http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=22156
<br />
 can easily be camped in Droga.  EASILY.  But it'll take some time.  If you take a full group of 55+ down to the Runri camp in Droga you could almost guarantee everyone to walk away from the camp with one of these:
<br />
http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=22130
<br />
And if the belt drops hopefully you have grabbed a group of people that are there with the intention of getting YOU the belt.  And with lull there are two other named placeholders in the vicinity of this guy you can also keep cleared.
<br />

<br />
Camping this item in Droga, and keeping the other PHs cleared and you and your group might have to spend a few days here, but I can tell you that you'll all walk away with a nice chunk of pocket change, several easily sellable items, and likely a couple levels higher.
<br />

<br />
Steelslave Bladed Boots are about 3kish.  Nice upgrade but not totally necessary for you right now.
<br />

<br />
Camp the Enchanted Sash, it is worth it, you'll get a good feel of the working of Droga.  By the time you get that belt you could have likely sold enough Legendary Daggers to fund any other upgrades you really want, gotten some really nice EXP, possibly have the gems you need for smithed armors, and learned some really good skills with your group..  Then if you really wanna save some cash Farm up the items to get some Smithed armors made, and you'll be in really good shape.   Then if you are feeling jumpy you and your group can start doing the other camps in Droga for Kingly Boots, Copper Hammer, Sword of the Bloodsworn etc etc.  
<br />

<br />
There are so many BIG CASH camps in Droga it isn't even funny.  Get to Droga and camp yourself some nice gear, then save all the plattage you make for upgrades you don't quite have access too.  You'll be beaming with pride if you camp and fight for all your gear.  Somthing about bought gear just isn't the same. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
